    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi!\n\nI'm experiencing an issue regarding the virtual LSP document color style not being visible, there's only an \"empty\" virtual line character visible (see the image below).\n\nBisecting leads to 4430c9a424 being the culprit.\n\n<img width=\"272\" height=\"111\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d0d9bca1-cf82-4e59-b4f6-18260dce39b8\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\n-- No plugins needed\n\n-- ADD INIT.LUA SETTINGS _NECESSARY_ FOR REPRODUCING THE ISSUE\nvim.lsp.config(\"cssls\", {\n    cmd = { \"vscode-css-language-server\", \"--stdio\" },\n    filetypes = { \"css\", \"scss\", \"less\" },\n    init_options = { provideFormatter = true },\n    root_markers = { \"package.json\", \".git\" },\n    settings = {\n        css = { validate = true },\n        scss = { validate = true },\n        less = { validate = true },\n    },\n})\nvim.lsp.enable(\"cssls\", true)\nvim.lsp.document_color.enable(true, nil, { style = \"virtual\" })\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe virtual character being visible like in the image below.\n\n<img width=\"214\" height=\"69\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6f386c03-6023-47e8-a974-b4dbf78d6d2a\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2619+g4430c9a424\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, LSP not supported in vim 9.2.148\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1, kitty 0.43.1, neovide 0.15.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty, xterm-kitty, xterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nDNF through the agriffis/neovim-nightly COPR repo, but building from source produces the issue as well",
